this is probably my favorite question I've ever gotten because people in my life used to call me crazy for putting my fan account on my resume for contacts I used to have a One Direction fan account with $150,000 followers I now work at a major record label sorry my friends eating an apple answer short I did include my fan account on my resume when getting these positions and in the interviews I would talk about it with that like any filters like obviously worked out very well for me but to get over that but think of the fact that if a man had a sports blog and he would post about hockey teams on his tiktok and Instagram he would go to a sports network he wanted to work for and would easily be like here's all my digital skills here's my accounts this is how much I know about the game I know the stats I know everything I'm passionate why wouldn't you want to hire someone like that so I kind of Applied that logic to being a fan of artists and it's essentially the same thing see this time and time again but the fact that we are fans of artists in this capacity and like I'll use the term fangirl we have advantages over other people and we have skills other people in the industry don't have because they have been through the experience is that we have through my fan account I learned audience acquisition audience maintenance content creation everything that employers at record labels in the digital space value now and honestly if you are trying to apply somewhere that looks down on you for being a fan you don't want to work there anyway because their years behind

column3: get ready with me for my first day of college as a 22-year-old so if you guys did the math correctly you probably realized that I should either be basically done school or done school but I am not this is my first day back in school after taking 4 years off there's honestly many reasons why I didn't go straight to school after high school honestly the main reason why was I wasn't sure like literally what I wanted to do and I didn't want to waste a bunch of money just for me to keep like switching programs and like you know not going for something I wanted to go for I've just been working these last few years and honestly deciding what I wanted to do with school nothing ever really stuck with me again I didn't want to just go into something to go into something I'm also very grateful for my parents yes they did push me to go to school but they also weren't like oh if you don't go to school or kicking you out or like this is not because I was working they are very understanding of the fact that I didn't go to school right after high school there was honestly I was like school is just not for me there's nothing I'm going to find interesting and like because like I just don't like any of this and this is when I started kind of like popping off on social media and I started doing content creating and I was like you know what why am I going to go to school if I'm making this money and like from content creating like I don't really need to go then I was like why don't I just go to something like to school for something that I actually enjoy which is like marketing so that is what I'm in school for I'm in school for advertising and marketing I'm like I already basically do this why not further my knowledge in it I have mixed emotions about going back to school just because I don't know I'm excited but I'm stressed like just everything that you can imagine us all the emotions going through my body right now but I know that after like the first week I'll get the hang of things I was honestly at one point like no I'm not going to go to school I'm ready like so far behind like it's been what 4 years why am I going to go to sleep this is just like embarrassing but at the end of the day like what is embarrassing about it I'm going to school to get an education or to further my education something that I want it's like pursue as a job so it's never too late I also do have a lot on my plate I'm not even going to lie because I have class basically every day of the week except for one day and I work four times a week and then I also do column3: I truly hated this healthy rice that my mom used to make for me as a kid and it's called Taco Bell but I got this new chocolate rice cooker for only 40 bucks on Facebook Marketplace so I tossed my older and decided to make this rice again to see if my very mature and very grown-up taste buds but I'm liking it to decades later like a mixed grain rice and there's no single recipe to make this but I put in some short grain white rice black rice brown rice sweet rice and some beans I soaked overnight you can also add barley and stuff but this is pretty much how my mom used to make it you know what I'm going to go apologize my mom right now because I think I like this more than white rice

I gave my family crabs this holiday season in the form of spicy raw marinated crabs or yum yum so I put off making these for a long time because I've never killed a crab before or a lobster before and I already felt this like wave of guilt building up but thankfully the screen on fish store had pre-cleaned Frozen Blue Crabs for discount so my conscience got to live to see another day and I was super excited about this dish because I get to reverse Korean mom my Korean mom because we never eaten up and to be fair it wasn't like a very popular Korean dish until Maurice only but now I get to make my mom something that she's never made before and now she gets to ask me for the rest of the recipe if she likes it so I'm pretty freaking stoked you should definitely serve these with some white rice and seaweed and you can squeeze the meat out onto the rice or something from the show dot with my family and honestly this was a parental validation I was looking for all year
